JYN00075
⿰骨衆 / ⿰骨眾
cung4 (zung1 in FSY1971)
FSY1971, P.74
FTL1974, P.21
FTL1996, P.53
WSL1941, P.48
ZWJ1988, P.202
  • In all sources, the right side of the word is 眾 or a variant of it.
  • FTL1974 says this is a variant of 㞞 U+379E, and mentions “國音常用字彙“.
  • However, the form in 國音常用字彙 (1932) is actually ⿰骨⿱血水. This form is seen in both the main content (P.237) and the radical-stroke index section (P.72).
  • 㞞 is a vulgar character in certain dialects, it means seman. So the form "⿰骨⿱血水", composed with 骨 (bone), 血 (blood) and 水 (water), makes sense as a compound ideograph (會意字). My guess is that since the word is basically unused in Cantonese, the form isn't persisted well. This reminds me of 𣚺. 𣚺 is composed by 未 (not yet) 成 (became) 母 (a mother), and 雞𣚺 means a virgin female chicken. But the left side of 𣚺 is written as "末" (final) in UCS2003. Same for 膥.
  • That said, ⿰骨眾 could also be interpreted as a phono-semantic compound character, in which 眾 is the phonetic component. Also, 衆 was also seen written as ⿳丿罒水.
  • 㞞 has another variant ⿰骨泉, which is interpreted as 骨 (bone) + 泉 (spring) or 骨 (bone) + 白 (white) + 水 (water/liquid). ⿰骨泉 is encoded in Ext-B (U+29A7A 𩩺).
  • This article mentions ⿱血⿰骨水, ⿰骨泉 and ⿰骨⿱血水. The answerer is certain that ⿰骨泉 is a variant of 㞞, and that ⿰骨泉 is also written as ⿰骨⿱血水 by elderlies in his/her county.
  • So ⿰骨泉 (𩩺) = ⿰骨眾 = ⿰骨⿱血水 = 㞞.
  • Also see JYN00173 (⿰骨⿱血水).

JYN00079
⿳艹⿻亜冖死
gwang1
FW1825, 利29
FW1838, 利29
FTL1974, P.45
  • This form is normally a variant of 薨, but source says it means "百蟲群飛聲".
  • I believe that the entry in FW (FW17XX, FW1828 and FW1838) is a misprinted form of “𦒃”. “𦒃” is a variant of “䎕” which means “飛聲。【玉篇】群鳥弄翅也。” (KangXi). 𦒃/䎕 pronounces the same as 轟, which reads [gwang1] in Cantonese. This matches the pronunciation given in FW.
  • FTL1974 states clearly that the form is inherited from FW.

JYN00159
⿰鼠余
N/A
LDY1916, preface-01
  • Probably because of the lack of certain movable types, the publisher used simple words to describe the corresponding ideographs. 余（旁舟）（又馬旁鼠旁） literally means 余 (with 舟 besides it) (also with 馬 and 鼠 besides it), and thus can be interpreted as “舟余 (艅)”, “馬余 (駼)” and “鼠余” respectively.
  • Also seen: GKJ-00643 (IRG WS2021).
  • The structure would be ⿺鼠余 for TC.
  • Extension J Working Draft: U+3345E
